resources.string:
This number shows the saturation
        of the colour on a scale from 0 to 255. You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This number shows the value
        of the colour on a scale from 0 to 255. You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This number shows the actual amount of red
        in the colour on a scale from 0 to 255. You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This number shows the actual amount of green
        in the colour on a scale from 0 to 255. You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This number shows the actual amount of blue
        in the colour on a scale from 0 to 255. You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This number shows the opacity of the background
        on a scale from 0 (transparent) to 255 (opaque). You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This slider adjusts the size
        of the seconds for the full screen clock:
        all the way to the left shows no seconds at all;
        intermediate values from left to right show seconds of increasing size;
        all the way to the right shows seconds the same size as
        the hours and minutes.

This slider adjusts the size of the seconds
        for the full screen clock:
        all the way to the bottom shows no seconds at all;
        intermediate values from bottom to top show seconds of increasing size;
        all the way to the top shows seconds the same size as the hours and minutes.

This number shows the maximum brightness
        of the full screen clock. See the README.md file for
        an explanation of how this works. You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This number shows the minimum brightness
        of the full screen clock. See the README.md file for
        an explanation of how this works. You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This number shows the minimum opacity
        of the full screen clock. See the README.md file for
        an explanation of how this works.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.

This number shows the ambient level in lux
        below which the full screen clock will reduce its brightness.
        You can edit the number.
        A single tap on the number will put the edit cursor where you tap;
        a double tap on the number will select the whole of it;
        a long tap on the number will display this message.
